2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a neural network approach for recognizing handwritten characters, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of neural networks for recognizing handwritten characters can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper discusses the conversion of handwritten data into electronic data, which can be relevant to the field of information retrieval. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The recognition of handwritten characters can also be relevant to the field of natural language processing, which falls under the domain of computation and language.
